ENTRY       EC 1.23.1.4                 Enzyme
NAME        (-)-lariciresinol reductase;
            pinoresinol/lariciresinol reductase;
            pinoresinol-lariciresinol reductases;
            (-)-pinoresinol-(-)-lariciresinol reductase;
            PLR
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Reducing C-O-C group as acceptor;
            With NADH or NADPH as donor (only sub-subclass identified to date)
SYSNAME     (+)-secoisolariciresinol:NADPH+ oxidoreductase
REACTION    (+)-secoisolariciresinol + NADP+ = (-)-lariciresinol + NADPH + H+ [RN:R10228]
ALL_REAC    R10228
SUBSTRATE   (+)-secoisolariciresinol [CPD:C20456];
            NADP+ [CPD:C00006]
PRODUCT     (-)-lariciresinol [CPD:C20454];
            NADPH [CPD:C00005];
            H+ [CPD:C00080]
COMMENT     The reaction is catalysed in vivo in the opposite direction to that shown. A multifunctional enzyme that also reduces (-)-pinoresinol [EC 1.23.1.3, (-)-pinoresinol reductase]. Isolated from the plants Thuja plicata (western red cedar) [1] and Linum corymbulosum [2].
